  m_Name: Level_01_Edzna
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  levelNumber: 1
  levelName: "Edzn\xE1 - House of the Itzaes"
  location: Campeche, Mexico
  levelDescription: "Long before the jungle reclaimed its stones, Edzn\xE1 thrived
    as a powerful Mayan city.\nIts name means \u201CHouse of the Itzaes\u201D, echoing
    through centuries of mystery.\n\nThe Great Temple\nRising 40 meters high, the
    main temple overlooks the plaza below \u2014 a watchtower of faith and power.\n\nThe
    Ball Court\nTwo long walls mark where sacred games were played.\nAbove, rooms
    once guarded images of the gods and ritual offerings.\n\nThrough Time\n- First
    settlers arrived around 400 BC\n- Reached its height by 200 AD\n- Flourished
    under the Calakmul polity\n- Blended styles of the Puuc tradition\n- Abandoned
    mysteriously by 1500 AD\n\nRediscovery\nLost to time until 1907, when explorers
    uncovered its ruins.\nBy 1958, excavation began.\nIn 1986, new life returned
    as Guatemalan refugees helped restore Edzn\xE1, guided by international aid.\n\nThe
    stones remember \u2014 even when the world forgets.\n"
  requiredStackHeight: 8
  oneStarScore: 100
  twoStarScore: 300
  threeStarScore: 500
  swingSpeedMultiplier: 1
  swingAmplitudeMultiplier: 1
